    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Those of us who speak plain English don't agonize over the meaning of words like benchmark, timetable, guidepost, yardstick, deadline, road map, regarding the Iraq War (On Language, William Safire, May 27).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Those of us who speak plain English don't agonize over the meaning of words like benchmark, timetable, guidepost, yardstick, deadline, road map, regarding the Iraq War (On Language, William Safire, May 27).</p>
        <p>In World War II, we knew exactly what ''unconditional surrender'' meant -- victory! And today we know what squabbling over terminology means in Iraq -- defeat!</p>
        <p>Warner B. Huck</p>
        <p>Hilton Head Island, S.C.</p>
      </block>
